Former Mpumalanga MEC Mandla Msibi and five others are facing murder and attempted murder charges. eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Two witnesses who implicated ANC Mpumalanga treasurer Mandla Msibi in the murder have withdrawn their statements. Msibi is facing two counts of murder and attempted murder for his alleged involvement at a Mbombela eatery last year. The two witnesses claim they were coerced by a regional ANC leader to implicate Msibi. READ: WATCH | ANC | Mandla Msibi to step aside They say they never saw who discharged the firearm that led to two people dying. Msibi recently stepped aside as treasurer just days after his election at the party’s provincial elective conference last month.